The paper discusses the integration of energy-efficient biomimetic designs into AI, which falls under the category of AI (cs.AI). It also mentions the need for AI to operate in extreme environments, which could involve robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the need for materials and technologies to provide energy, which could fall under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET) and machine learning (cs.MA) for optimizing energy usage.
